From: Carlo Szelinsky <github@szelinsky.de>
Subject: net: pse-pd: add poll helper and LED triggers

Combine three related changes for PSE controllers that lack IRQ support:

1. Extract the event handling loop from pse_isr() into a shared
   pse_handle_events() function, and add devm_pse_poll_helper() as a
   generic poll-based alternative to the IRQ path. The poll interval is
   configurable via the DT property "poll-interval-ms" (default 500ms).

2. Add per-PI "delivering" and "enabled" LED triggers to the PSE core.
   LED state is updated from pse_handle_events() whenever the IRQ or
   poll path detects a state change, reusing the existing notification
   pipeline. LED triggers are registered based on DT-described PIs
   (not rdev) so they work before any PHY claims a PSE control.

3. Add dt-bindings documentation for poll-interval-ms.

Signed-off-by: Carlo Szelinsky <github@szelinsky.de>
